medical need, prompting many, including members of the Louisiana House of
Representatives, to approach emerging therapies with a more open perspective, while still
prioritizing patient safety; and
WHEREAS, rising cancer rates in Louisiana, and reports of residents seeking
unverified sources of fenbendazole, raise important public health considerations that warrant
formal evaluation by the state's chief health officer; and
WHEREAS, the expertise of the state surgeon general in public health policy and
emerging therapies is essential to determining whether fenbendazole could offer a viable,
expedited treatment option for patients facing limited alternatives.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request the surgeon general of this state to do
all of the following:
(1) Provide a professional assessment and guidance regarding the feasibility of
advancing fenbendazole or similar treatments toward potential human authorization for the
treatment of cancer or other medical conditions, including any appropriate state-level steps
this state could take to support, or advocate for, further scientific review.
(2) Develop a recommended plan for engaging federal authorities, including the
United States Food and Drug Administration, to expedite evaluation of fenbendazole or
similar treatments through compassionate use protocols, expanded access programs, or
prioritization in clinical trials, while ensuring patient safety and adherence to evidence-based
standards.
(3) Submit a written report of findings and recommendations to the House
Committee on Health and Welfare no later than February 1, 2027.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
surgeon general of this state and the secretary of the Louisiana Department of Health.
